Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.00,0:00:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,从此刻起,我们就和我们生命终结的那一刻,联系在了一起\N{\rasEng}From the moment we're conceived to the day we take our last breath,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.12,0:00:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,科学,随着使用,触及到了我们每一个人\N{\rasEng}science,and the way we use it,touches every one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.96,0:00:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,科学被赋予了巨大的能力来拯救或孕育生命\N{\rasEng}Science has given immense power to save and nurture life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.48,0:00:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但是变化的步伐如此之大,以至于我们很少花点时间\N{\rasEng}But the pace of change is so great that we don't often take time
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.12,0:00:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,停下来,看看我们已经走了多远\N{\rasEng}to stop and appreciate how far we've come.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.68,0:00:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是,我想和你分享这个时代最重要的十项科学进步的原因\N{\rasEng}That's why I want to share with you ten of the most important scientific advances of our time,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.64,0:00:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,并且揭示一些摆在我们面前的事情\N{\rasEng}and reveal some of the things that might just lie ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.32,0:00:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个节目的最后,我会要求你投票\N{\rasEng}At the end of the programme I'll be asking you to vote
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.60,0:00:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,选出最能改变你的世界的进步\N{\rasEng}for the advance you think has done the most to change your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.08,0:00:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,这对我们的社会有着巨大的冲击\N{\rasEng}It's had a massive impact on our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.32,0:00:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,它确实改变了你的生活,不是吗？\N{\rasEng}It's really changed your life,hasn't it？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.36,0:00:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,所以,你是完美的仿生女人？\N{\rasEng}So you're the perfect bionic woman？ Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.68,0:00:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,还是赢家？嗯,这取决于你.\N{\rasEng}And the winner？ Well,it's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.00,0:01:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\b1\fn方正姚体\fs76\pos(620,507)}科学如何改变我们的世界
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.94,0:01:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这是个人的一小步,却是人类的一大步.\N{\rasEng}It's one small step for man,one giant leap for mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.72,0:01:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,过去50年中已经看到科学改造我们的世界.\N{\rasEng}The last 50 years has seen science transform our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.84,0:01:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,半个世纪以来,它战胜了无数的疾病\N{\rasEng}In half a century,it's tackled countless diseases,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.32,0:01:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,把人送上月球\N{\rasEng}put men on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.36,0:01:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,彻底改变我们的沟通方式.\N{\rasEng}and completely changed the way we communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.52,0:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我的科学十大进步.\N{\rasEng}These are my top ten advances.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.28,0:01:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,有些可能是你期望的,有些可能会让你惊讶.\N{\rasEng}Some things you may expect,others you may find more surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.60,0:01:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,第一项科学进步,差点就没被包括在我的十大进步中,\N{\rasEng}The first advance to take place in my top ten almost didn't make it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.56,0:01:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,因为它太古老了！\N{\rasEng}because it's very nearly too old!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.64,0:02:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个一些女性喜欢,但又假装不感兴趣的\N{\rasEng}There are some women who prefer at least to pretend they're not interested in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.88,0:02:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,喜欢被男性亲近\N{\rasEng}And who like to be approached by the man.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.44,0:02:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但是,对于一切的伟大时代\N{\rasEng}But for all its great age,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.60,0:02:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,它让很多人非常高兴\N{\rasEng}it's made a lot of people extremely happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.08,0:02:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,啊,我怎么就失去了贞操！\N{\rasEng}Ah,how I lost my virginity!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.16,0:02:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,老天爷,我母亲就有一个合适的\N{\rasEng}Cor blimey. My mother would have had a fit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.76,0:02:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我们有一场比赛,我和这个女孩,看谁能把它首先移开,这很可怕！\N{\rasEng}We had a race,me and this girl,to see who could have it off first. It was terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.92,0:02:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们都玩得很高兴\N{\rasEng}But we were having a wonderful time!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.72,0:02:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,当我还是一个医科学生时,\N{\rasEng}When I was a medical student,which is longer ago than I actually care to mention,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.60,0:02:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,发生了一场技术革命\N{\rasEng}there was a revolution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.32,0:02:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,有些人认为这改变了我们的社会.那就是避孕药.\N{\rasEng}which some people claim transformed our society. It was,of course,the contraceptive pill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,1961年,这小小的药片诞生于英国\N{\rasEng}In 1961,the Pill was released in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.84,0:02:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这个日期印在了药片的每一面\N{\rasEng}The day is printed by the side of every pill.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.72,0:02:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,并让她能记起这是哪一天,\N{\rasEng}And providing she can remember what day it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.80,0:03:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,女性可以非常确定今天她吃药没有\N{\rasEng}a woman can be quite sure whether or not she has taken today's pill.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.52,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,制造商尽最大努力使它们万无一失\N{\rasEng}The manufacturers do their best to make them foolproof -
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们不想失去他们的声誉,或者称之为"飞行员的错误"\N{\rasEng}they don't want to lose their reputation over what might be called "pilot's error".
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.80,0:03:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,今天,我们把它视为理所当然,但在当时,这是革命性的.\N{\rasEng}Today we take it for granted,but for that first generation,it was revolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我是个学生的老师\N{\rasEng}I was a student teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.96,0:03:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在当时,并且,嗯\N{\rasEng}during that time,and,er,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.52,0:03:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,学校周围到处都是\N{\rasEng}it got round in college
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.48,0:03:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,有一个医生在Doncaster发放避孕药,\N{\rasEng}that there was a certain doctor in Doncaster that would give the Pill,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.32,0:03:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们都抄捷径跑去.\N{\rasEng}so we all made a beeline for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.08,0:03:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣的是,所有的病人,我们都称之为“太太“\N{\rasEng}Interestingly enough,all the patients,we were all called "Mrs"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.92,0:03:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,当你被喊进去看医生.\N{\rasEng}when you were called in to see the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,在那儿,你就不是“小姐”了\N{\rasEng}You weren't "Miss" even there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们去一个私人诊所,还要遮掩一下,所以我带上一个纸袋.\N{\rasEng}We knew there was one private clinic,except you had to pay for it,so I had to take a paper round.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.84,0:03:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,避孕药在社会大变革的时候爆发式的出现,\N{\rasEng}The Pill exploded onto the scene at a time of great social upheaval,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.88,0:04:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,而它自己也成了这一巨大变化的一部分.\N{\rasEng}and itself became a huge part of that change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.36,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉被解放了.从怀孕的恐惧中解放出来,太不可思议了.\N{\rasEng}I felt quite liberated. Just to be free of that fear of becoming pregnant was amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我意识到我已经控制了自己的生活\N{\rasEng}I was aware that I was taking control of my own life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,当时报纸上有很多关于避孕药的报道"哦,它会让女性行为不检点"\N{\rasEng}There were lots of things in the newspapers about the Pill,"Oh,it'll make women tarty,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.44,0:04:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,所有这些事,你知道.对我来说并不是那样.\N{\rasEng}and everything,you know. It wasn't like that for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以有计划的安排,对我来说非常重要的孩子和事业.\N{\rasEng}I could plan my children and my career,which was so important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但是没有人预见到的是,使用避孕药把生育推迟\N{\rasEng}But what nobody foresaw was that the Pill meant that more women
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,的妇女会有更多不孕不育的风险.\N{\rasEng}have tended to leave child-bearing later and risk infertility.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.76,0:04:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是它能让更多的人自由的规划、平衡、改变,让生活变得更好.\N{\rasEng}But that freedom to plan has,on balance,changed most people's lives for the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.80,0:04:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这个原因,避孕药位列我的十大科技进步之一.\N{\rasEng}And for that reason,the Pill has to be in my top ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.88,0:04:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它很小,但它的对我们的社会产生了巨大的冲击.\N{\rasEng}It's tiny but it's had a massive impact on our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.80,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,它产生的影响是过去50年最重要的进步之一.\N{\rasEng}Its liberating influence has been one of the most important advances in the last 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.52,0:05:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,正如避孕药在二十世纪六十年代,改变了妇女的生活,\N{\rasEng}Just as the Pill transformed women's lives in the 1960s,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.32,0:05:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,科学有一次改变了我们和避孕的关系.\N{\rasEng}science is changing our relationship with contraception again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill和Rachel要开始试验一种新的避孕方式\N{\rasEng}Bill and Rachel are just about to start a trial
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.24,0:05:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不需要像以前那样每天采取措施.\N{\rasEng}for a new contraceptive that doesn't need to be taken every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你已经有了三个孩子,你有怀孕时,每次服用避孕药？\N{\rasEng}You've had three children,and you got pregnant when on the Pill each time？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.72,0:05:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,是的.与避孕药无关,只与我们的做法有关.\N{\rasEng}Yeah. Nothing to do with the Pill,just to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.36,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你没有正确使用？这是一个.\N{\rasEng}You didn't take it properly？ That's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.36,0:05:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,你试过什么避孕方法？\N{\rasEng}So what methods of contraception have you tried？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经试过节欲,因为他在海军,所以他常常外出工作一段时间.\N{\rasEng}We've tried abstinence,cos he was in the Navy,so that worked for a while,with him going away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.24,0:05:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们试过在开始的时候用避孕套.\N{\rasEng}We tried condoms briefly in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.56,0:05:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么你不想再吃避孕药了？\N{\rasEng}And why didn't you want to take the Pill any more？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我真的很不接受它\N{\rasEng}I'm really not good at taking it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.96,0:05:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我很放心不应该有不同化学物质,肯定知道我会忘记压力.\N{\rasEng}and I'd be relieved to not have different chemicals,and the stress of knowing I'd forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.08,0:06:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you didn't mind your husband having the chemicals？ No. Bash on.\N{\rasEng}And you didn't mind your husband having the chemicals？ No. Bash on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.88,0:06:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be great for him to take some responsibility.\N{\rasEng}I think it would be great for him to take some responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.48,0:06:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The contraceptive they're about to try is actually for Bill,not Rachel.\N{\rasEng}The contraceptive they're about to try is actually for Bill,not Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,I know what you might be thinking -\N{\rasEng}Now,I know what you might be thinking -
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.84,0:06:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and if I were a woman,I might not trust a man,\N{\rasEng}and if I were a woman,I might not trust a man,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.56,0:06:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,even a reliable fireman like Bill to take the Pill,either.\N{\rasEng}even a reliable fireman like Bill to take the Pill,either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.32,0:06:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But this pill\N{\rasEng}But this pill
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.28,0:06:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually a course of injections which will leave Bill temporarily infertile.\N{\rasEng}is actually a course of injections which will leave Bill temporarily infertile.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.52,0:06:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So what on earth made you take part in this trial？\N{\rasEng}So what on earth made you take part in this trial？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mmm... For me,it's just about being able to take over\N{\rasEng}Mmm... For me,it's just about being able to take over
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the role of contraception from Rachel,and me being responsible for that,\N{\rasEng}the role of contraception from Rachel,and me being responsible for that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than it all being left to Rache.\N{\rasEng}rather than it all being left to Rache.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And did the side-effects that they talk about\N{\rasEng}And did the side-effects that they talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.92,0:06:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,on the male contraception worry you？\N{\rasEng}on the male contraception worry you？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are a few side effects that they did warn us about,like weight gain,\N{\rasEng}There are a few side effects that they did warn us about,like weight gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.40,0:07:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,acne,irritability.\N{\rasEng}acne,irritability.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did they tell you you might develop breasts？\N{\rasEng}Did they tell you you might develop breasts？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,They did say that. Yes.\N{\rasEng}They did say that. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.20,0:07:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a fireman,aren't you？ I am.\N{\rasEng}You're a fireman,aren't you？ I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you discuss it with your mates at work？\N{\rasEng}Did you discuss it with your mates at work？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Strangely,no.\N{\rasEng}Strangely,no.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Why？ I mean... the ribbing I'll get,never mind...\N{\rasEng}Why？ I mean... the ribbing I'll get,never mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.28,0:07:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really macho environment.\N{\rasEng}It's a really macho environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.88,0:07:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It is I suppose,it's fertility and a guy,like,you know,I'm really butch...\N{\rasEng}Yeah. It is I suppose,it's fertility and a guy,like,you know,I'm really butch...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.48,0:07:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you understand the science of how it actually works？ I don't.\N{\rasEng}And do you understand the science of how it actually works？ I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.12,0:07:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to know？ Yes,please.\N{\rasEng}Would you like to know？ Yes,please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.08,0:07:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me explain it to you.\N{\rasEng}Let me explain it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.16,0:07:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually quite surprising,and in some ways\N{\rasEng}It's actually quite surprising,and in some ways
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.92,0:07:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not dissimilar from the female pill,the oral contraception that women take.\N{\rasEng}it's not dissimilar from the female pill,the oral contraception that women take.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And essentially,it really works in the brain,so if this is a body,\N{\rasEng}And essentially,it really works in the brain,so if this is a body,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the brain sends out a signal\N{\rasEng}the brain sends out a signal
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.04,0:07:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to make an egg or make a sperm,OK？\N{\rasEng}to make an egg or make a sperm,OK？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.92,0:08:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,the pill is a hormone which inhibits the brain by telling it the egg is already being made\N{\rasEng}Now,the pill is a hormone which inhibits the brain by telling it the egg is already being made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.20,0:08:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's not being made,so the brain thinks the woman is ovulating so it stops sending the message,\N{\rasEng}when it's not being made,so the brain thinks the woman is ovulating so it stops sending the message,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.52,0:08:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's exactly what happens with the male contraception,too,so if you're given the male hormone,\N{\rasEng}and that's exactly what happens with the male contraception,too,so if you're given the male hormone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.64,0:08:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that tells the brain,"I'm making lots of sperm,"\N{\rasEng}that tells the brain,"I'm making lots of sperm,"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.24,0:08:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,so it just shuts down. So it's quite an elegant idea,\N{\rasEng}so it just shuts down. So it's quite an elegant idea,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.28,0:08:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that feedback is\N{\rasEng}and that feedback is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.28,0:08:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the most interesting examples in biology of how the body works.\N{\rasEng}one of the most interesting examples in biology of how the body works.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.12,0:08:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea is that the injections will deal with Bill's biological feedback for months at a time.\N{\rasEng}The idea is that the injections will deal with Bill's biological feedback for months at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这是他的主意.\N{\rasEng}This was his idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我的10大科技中的第一项——避孕药,诞生于大变革的六十年代,\N{\rasEng}So the first entry on my list is the Pill - revolutionary in the '60s,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在在之后的50年里仍然不断地改进自身.\N{\rasEng}and still reinventing itself almost 50 years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,太奇妙了\N{\rasEng}Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.84,0:08:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的下一个科学进步也显著的影响了我们的生活-\N{\rasEng}My next advance has also had a dramatic impact on our lives -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.24,0:09:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上,它是如此的重要,以至于在我的十大科学进步名单中,扮演了重要的角色\N{\rasEng}in fact,it's so significant that it's played a part in almost all of the other inventions on my list.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.96,0:09:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,当我还在念书时,我在一个无线电厂里工作\N{\rasEng}When I was a schoolboy,I worked in a radio factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.68,0:09:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Benzimra先生一周付我5英镑\N{\rasEng}I was being paid five pounds a week by Mr Benzimra,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.76,0:09:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,把密密麻麻的零部件焊上这样的印刷电路板\N{\rasEng}a princely sum,to solder little components onto a printed circuit board like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,很快,我意识到这就像横渡大西洋般困难,而一个人改变了整个进程\N{\rasEng}Little did I realise that across the Atlantic,a man was going to revolutionise the whole process.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.68,0:09:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,一个名叫Jack Kilby的工程师发明了一种缩小这些部件的方法.\N{\rasEng}An engineer called Jack Kilby found a way to shrink all these components
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.88,0:09:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,把这些部件都集中在一个很小的东西里\N{\rasEng}into one extraordinary,and tiny thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.92,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这个,不起眼的微型芯片\N{\rasEng}It's this,the humble microchip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.28,0:09:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,自从50年前发明了这个,\N{\rasEng}And since its invention 50 years ago,there's been more medical
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.80,0:09:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在医学和科技方面取得的进步,比人类历史上任他何其时期都多\N{\rasEng}and scientific progress than in any other period in human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.44,0:10:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,微型芯片是我的科学十大进步之一.从我们早上醒来\N{\rasEng}The microchip has to be in our top ten. From the moment we wake up
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,到我们晚上睡觉,它影响了我们生活中的方方面面\N{\rasEng}to the moment we go to bed,it affects every part of our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.88,0:10:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,没有微芯片,我们就没有笔记本电脑.\N{\rasEng}Without the microchip,there would be no laptop,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.52,0:10:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,没有银行卡,没有手机.\N{\rasEng}no cash card,no mobile phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.08,0:10:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,简单的说,没有微型芯片,我们将仍然生活在20世纪70年代\N{\rasEng}In short,without the microchip,we'd still be living in the 1970s.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.96,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,让我惊讶的是,当年我焊接的老式电路板的所有这些部件\N{\rasEng}It amazes me that today all those elements of the old electronic circuit board
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,现在只能在显微镜下看见\N{\rasEng}I soldered together as a schoolboy can only be seen down a microscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只是把它们做的更小了\N{\rasEng}And now the technology is set to make it even smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.48,0:10:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我在伦敦纳米技术中心\N{\rasEng}I'm in the London Centre for Nanotechnology,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.08,0:11:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这里用最小的粒子来制造东西\N{\rasEng}where they make the smallest particles that are possible to be made.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.00,0:11:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,因为这个原因,我得穿上防尘服,因为哪怕是空气中的\N{\rasEng}And the reason why I'm wearing the garb is because any skin cell
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.32,0:11:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,皮肤细胞都会污染他们的东西.\N{\rasEng}in the atmosphere would contaminate what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.88,0:11:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的指尖上\N{\rasEng}And here on my fingertip
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.20,0:11:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是一个小小的电路板\N{\rasEng}is a little electronic chip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.76,0:11:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个电路板上他们能放下5千万个晶体管\N{\rasEng}On this chip,they can fit 50 million transistors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.48,0:11:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这个,下一代微电路版\N{\rasEng}This,the next generation of mini-miracles,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.00,0:11:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,目前它是最小的.\N{\rasEng}is as small as it gets...for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这个晶圆上的每一个电子元件都比病毒还小\N{\rasEng}Each electronic component in these circuits is smaller than a virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.64,0:11:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着微型设备将会像病毒一样,\N{\rasEng}And that miniaturisation means that chips,like viruses,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.56,0:11:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,以我们无法想象的方式进入我们的生活\N{\rasEng}are getting closer to us than we could have possibly imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.00,0:11:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,现在这儿就有一样东西.这个微型芯片完全由可食用的物质制成.\N{\rasEng}Now,here's a thing. This microchip is made of a substance which is entirely edible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.48,0:11:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,因此一旦你吞下它,它就会被胃酸分解\N{\rasEng}So when you swallow it,it gets dissolved by the acid
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.52,0:11:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,然后发送一个信号到你胳膊上的接收器上\N{\rasEng}in your stomach,and it sends a signal to a plaster on your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是胳膊上的接收器 - ow! -\N{\rasEng}And the plaster on your arm - ow! -
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.80,0:12:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,这个小小的设备就像一个接收机,如果你没有按时吃下你的药片\N{\rasEng}has got this little device like a radio,and if you haven't taken your pill...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.76,0:12:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我的手机会得到这个消息,并且说"你今天没有按时吃药"\N{\rasEng}I get a message on my phone saying,"You haven't your pill today."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.60,0:12:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,但是任何技术都是一柄双刃剑\N{\rasEng}But there's a darker side to all technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.28,0:12:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,微型芯片的广泛应用确实带来一些问题\N{\rasEng}The sheer proliferation of the microchip does bring some concerns.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.36,0:12:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我站在皮卡迪里广场,你可要知道在50码范围内\N{\rasEng}It's worth considering that within 50 yards of where I'm standing in Piccadilly Circus,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,至少有50部监视摄像机记录下我的每一个动作\N{\rasEng}there must be at least 50 surveillance cameras recording every movement we make,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.52,0:12:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这些海量的数据我们并没有管理好.\N{\rasEng}amassing a huge amount of data over which we have no control.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.96,0:12:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们如何处理这些问题,是一个日益严峻的挑战.\N{\rasEng}How we deal with these issues is an increasing challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.16,0:12:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,存储的个人数据在很大程度上是不受管制,\N{\rasEng}Storage of personal data is largely unregulated,and fraud,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.96,0:12:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在虚拟世界中诈骗、盗窃和丢失个人数据,让越来越多的人开始担忧\N{\rasEng}theft and loss of privacy in the virtual world worries many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.40,0:12:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,尽管如此,微芯片仍然在我的科学进步名单中\N{\rasEng}But in spite of all this,the chip is on my list,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.56,0:12:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,我们不能否认,没有它很多其他领域的进展将会变得不可能\N{\rasEng}and we shouldn't forget that without it,many of the other advances wouldn't have been possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.16,0:13:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,包括下面这一个\N{\rasEng}Including this next one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.84,0:13:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,第三项科学进步是我故事中的一个设备\N{\rasEng}At number three on my list is a device in whose story I,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.72,0:13:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,或者说是我的兔子Wilhelmina,在这儿扮演一个主角\N{\rasEng}or rather my rabbit Wilhelmina,played here by an actor,had a starring role.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧,一个角色,反正\N{\rasEng}Well,a role,anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.80,0:13:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我在酒吧里和一些物理学的朋友喝了一晚上的啤酒,\N{\rasEng}I met some physics friends in the bar having a beer one evening,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.68,0:13:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,他们说“我们刚刚建造了这台有着不计其数电线的机器”\N{\rasEng}and they said,"We've just built this machine with lots of wire
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,还有天花板蜡和老式电视屏幕\N{\rasEng}"and string and ceiling wax and an old television screen
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.20,0:13:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,它叫做磁共振图像机\N{\rasEng}"and it's called a Magnetic Resonance Image machine,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.40,0:13:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,"你想把你的兔子放进去吗？"\N{\rasEng}"and would you like to put your rabbit in it？"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.92,0:13:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们就下到了Hammersmith医院的地下室\N{\rasEng}So we went down to the sub-basement of Hammersmith Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.48,0:13:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们很温柔的把Wilhelmina放了进去\N{\rasEng}and we put Wilhelmina gently into the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.56,0:13:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我有一点点但心它,经过20分钟的烹饪\N{\rasEng}I was a bit worried about it,and then after 20 minutes of cooking,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.08,0:13:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们得到了一张照片,看起来有点像这个.\N{\rasEng}we got a photograph,and it looked a bit like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.00,0:13:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,只是一片模糊\N{\rasEng}Just a blur.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.32,0:13:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我并没有意识到这将是这个时代的一场革命\N{\rasEng}And I didn't have the sense to realise that this was going to be quite revolutionary in its time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.08,0:14:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我想我的兔子是第一个拍这种照片的活体生物之一.\N{\rasEng}I think my pet rabbit was one of the first living organisms to be photographed like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.56,0:14:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这项技术,这在当时刚刚起步,后来成为核磁共振扫描仪.\N{\rasEng}And the technology,which was then in its infancy,went on to become the MRI scanner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.40,0:14:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,在我的大部分医学生涯,X射线是检查人体最有效的手段\N{\rasEng}For much of my career in medicine,X-rays were the most effective way of looking inside the human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.40,0:14:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但是它并没有给出除骨头以外其他器官的清晰图像\N{\rasEng}But they didn't give a particularly clear image of all the organs beyond our bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,核磁共振扫描改变了一切.\N{\rasEng}MRI scanning changed all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.00,0:14:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,工程师最初用核磁共振来检查金属内部.\N{\rasEng}Engineers first used MRI to look inside metals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,现在我们可以直接看到生物组织.\N{\rasEng}Now we're able see directly into living tissues
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.60,0:14:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这给了我们不可思议的新视野,来观察最复杂的人体组织结构.\N{\rasEng}and that's given amazing new insights into the most complicated organ in the human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.52,0:14:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得很谦逊,而这个空间,这个没有生命的物体,\N{\rasEng}I find it really rather humbling that this space,this inanimate object,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这个大脑曾经是某个人感受到愤怒、悲伤、爱的地方.\N{\rasEng}this brain was once the place where somebody felt angry,felt sad,and loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.96,0:14:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,另人惊讶的是,直到最近,我们都不知道它是如何真正工作.\N{\rasEng}And the extraordinary thing is that until quite recently,we had no idea how it was really working.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.60,0:15:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,令人振奋的研究来自剑桥大学,利用MRI（核磁共振成像扫描仪）,研究大脑如何思考.\N{\rasEng}Exciting research at the University of Cambridge is using the MRI scanner to see how the mind works.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.48,0:15:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,罗伯特,你好.很高兴见到你.\N{\rasEng}Robert,hello. Nice to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.96,0:15:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,在隔壁扫描室的是一个志愿者,我从来没见过他.\N{\rasEng}In the scanner next door is a willing volunteer I've never met.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.28,0:15:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我要你朝这边.而不是看窗户？\N{\rasEng}I want you to face this way. And not to look in the window？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.40,0:15:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这样我就看不到你的课题.\N{\rasEng}So I can't see your subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.92,0:15:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,问一些简单的是或否的问题,\N{\rasEng}By asking some simple yes or no questions,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我要试着找出一些关于他的,或者是她.\N{\rasEng}I'm going to try to find out a bit about him. Or her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,如果在扫描仪里的人想要表达“是”\N{\rasEng}If the person in the scanner is trying to convey a yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,你就会看到运动前皮层周围呈现亮红色\N{\rasEng}you'll see a bright red area of activity around his pre-motor cortex,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.20,0:15:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,顶部的右边,头部的中间.\N{\rasEng}right at the top,in the middle of the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.44,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,如果在扫描仪里的人想要说“否”\N{\rasEng}If the person in the scanner is trying to convey a no,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.60,0:15:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你会看到同样的区域呈现高亮,\N{\rasEng}you'll see the same area of the brain lighting up
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.12,0:15:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,只不过变成了蓝绿色.\N{\rasEng}but it will be a blue-green colour.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.04,0:15:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你是男性吗？\N{\rasEng}Are you a man？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.00,0:15:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,该你了.\N{\rasEng}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.52,0:15:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我很确信此时这个人在表达“是”\N{\rasEng}I'm pretty confident this person is conveying a yes at this stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.48,0:16:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你超过六英尺高？\N{\rasEng}Are you over six foot high？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.36,0:16:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,现在是绿色,他在说“否”\N{\rasEng}He's now got a green area,so this is signalling a no answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.16,0:16:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这就意味着这个人实际上没有六英尺高.\N{\rasEng}which would mean that actually this man is shorter than six foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们并不能实际看到大脑说“是”或“否”\N{\rasEng}We can't actually see the brain think yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.20,0:16:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这对于一台MRI（核磁共振成像仪）来说并不是一件太难的事.\N{\rasEng}That would be too difficult even for an MRI machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.24,0:16:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们要求志愿者想像打网球\N{\rasEng}What our volunteer was asked to do was to imagine playing tennis
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.12,0:16:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,当他回答“是”并照做时,大脑的相关区域\N{\rasEng}when he wants to say yes,and when he does,the area of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.64,0:16:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,运动和想象,他的运动前皮层\N{\rasEng}which deals with movement,his motor cortex,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,显示出活跃增加,用MRI很容易看到.\N{\rasEng}shows increased activity,and that is easy for the MRI to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们最后一个问题.\N{\rasEng}And this is our last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.24,0:16:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,你有胡子吗？\N{\rasEng}Do you have facial hair？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.80,0:16:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,相关区域再次活跃起来.\N{\rasEng}Again,pretty obvious activation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.20,0:16:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我会说这家伙的要么留着胡须要么有胡子.\N{\rasEng}I would say that this guy's either got a beard or a moustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.04,0:16:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi!\N{\rasEng}Hi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.92,0:16:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,非常感谢你,我是罗伯特.温斯顿\N{\rasEng}Thank you so much. I'm Robert Winston.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.28,0:16:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,你肯定没有六英尺高.\N{\rasEng}You're certainly not six-foot high,we got that right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.08,0:17:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,最近的一项研究使用这种技术,使我们可以观测并与一些\N{\rasEng}One recent study using this technique has given us an insight into communication
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.48,0:17:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,被认为是永久植物人的病人进行的沟通.\N{\rasEng}with some patients in what was thought to be a permanent vegetative state.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.32,0:17:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,最近我们看到了一个病人,他在这种状态下已经五年了,\N{\rasEng}We've seen a patient recently,who'd actually been in that situation for five years
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.88,0:17:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,他能够以这种技术来传达是”或“不是”的反应.\N{\rasEng}and he was able to use this technique to convey yes and no responses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.56,0:17:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这当然不是所有病人的情况,但我们现在知道,\N{\rasEng}It's certainly not the case for all patients,but we now know there are a sub-group of these patients
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.92,0:17:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这些患者中的一些有可能比我们想象能做的更多.\N{\rasEng}who probably can do more than we think they can.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.28,0:17:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这很可怕,不是？\N{\rasEng}It's quite scary,isn't it？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.48,0:17:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,难道你不觉得真的很惊人,\N{\rasEng}Do you not find that really quite amazing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.04,0:17:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,而且符合我们的人性？\N{\rasEng}but also very on the edge of our humanity？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.08,0:17:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,它是,它是许多人发现很难去思考,\N{\rasEng}It is and it is something that many people find quite difficult to think about,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你的思想会被困在你的身体,而无法交流.\N{\rasEng}the idea that you could be trapped inside your body and unable to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.88,0:17:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,幸运的是我们找到了一种方法,让一些病人能够绕过这种困境.\N{\rasEng}Hopefully we've found a way where some of these patients can get around that issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.16,0:17:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这其实是测量你体内血液流量的变化.\N{\rasEng}Essentially what you're measuring is changes in blood flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.48,0:17:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们观测大脑中的活跃区域.\N{\rasEng}We're looking at the areas of the brain that are working hardest.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.36,0:18:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这些活跃区域需要更多的血液来提供氧气,这也正是我们测量的.\N{\rasEng}They're drawing blood,which is delivering oxygen and that's what we're measuring.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.40,0:18:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我不可能看到有人用这台机器说,"他认为我是个白痴. "\N{\rasEng}I couldn't look at somebody with this machine and say,"He thinks I am a complete moron."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.72,0:18:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不,也许那是真的,但是至少你不会知道.\N{\rasEng}No,that might be true,but at least you won't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.48,0:18:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,无论如何MRI是我们研究大脑如何思考的重要途径.\N{\rasEng}Undoubtedly,the MRI machine has been the most important way of seeing how our brain works.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.88,0:18:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,它本身就有资格作为过去50年最重要的科学进步之一.\N{\rasEng}And that alone qualifies it as one of the most significant advances in the last 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.36,0:18:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,对于我来说,它脱颖而出的是将它非凡的能力\N{\rasEng}But what really makes it stand out for me is its extraordinary ability
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.28,0:18:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,用于医学上来改善生命.\N{\rasEng}to transform lives through its use in medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.12,0:18:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,17岁的Elyse Westrip在她11岁时,就患有严重的癫痫症.\N{\rasEng}17-year-old Elyse Westrip has had severe epilepsy since she was 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,近来,核磁共振扫描发现,癫痫是由于大脑肿瘤造成的.\N{\rasEng}MRI scans have recently revealed that the seizures are due to a brain tumour.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.72,0:18:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,明亮的区域就是异常的区域.\N{\rasEng}This bright area here is the area that is abnormal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.80,0:18:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们现在要做的就是确定如何关闭该区域\N{\rasEng}What we need to do now is determine how close
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.48,0:18:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,同时又避免影响其重要功能.\N{\rasEng}that area to be removed is to parts that carry out vital functions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.52,0:19:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然肿瘤可以摘除,\N{\rasEng}Though it's been decided that the tumour can be removed,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.44,0:19:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,但坏消息是这个肿瘤非常靠近她的视神经.\N{\rasEng}the bad news is that it's dangerously close to her optic nerve.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,手术有可能导致部分失明.\N{\rasEng}The operation carries the risk of partial blindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,但是对于Elyse来说,这个险值得冒.\N{\rasEng}But for Elyse,it's a risk worth taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.44,0:19:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我试着忘记风险,\N{\rasEng}I'm trying to forget the risks
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.84,0:19:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,只想积极的,\N{\rasEng}and just think positive,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.48,0:19:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,手术后好起来的事情.\N{\rasEng}the good things about having the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.60,0:19:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我感到我正越来越好,\N{\rasEng}I feel I'm going to get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.88,0:19:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我可以改变我现在的生活,恢复到以前那样.\N{\rasEng}I can change my life back to how it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.56,0:19:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,癫痫变得很糟糕,我决定提前离开学校,因为我应付不了了.\N{\rasEng}The epilepsy got so bad I decided to leave school early because I couldn't cope any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.32,0:19:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我的病我非常烦恼.\N{\rasEng}I just got upset a lot that I was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,它在很大程度上改变了我的生活.\N{\rasEng}It did change my life a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.96,0:20:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,肿瘤位于Elyse大脑内部5厘米处.\N{\rasEng}The tumour is buried five centimetres into Elyse's brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.88,0:20:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在过去,这种手术\N{\rasEng}In the past,patients undergoing this operation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.52,0:20:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,会让病人承担很大的脑损伤风险.\N{\rasEng}would have run a significant risk of suffering brain damage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.20,0:20:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但是感谢MRI技术的使用,Elyse将面对的风险大大降低了.\N{\rasEng}But thanks to MRI,the risk to Elyse is greatly reduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在 MRI 新的应用中,扫描得到的图像映射到外科医生的显微镜中,\N{\rasEng}In a new use of MRI,the scans are mapped onto an image seen in the surgeon's microscope,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.04,0:20:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,这可以引导医生避开正常的脑组织切除肿瘤.\N{\rasEng}and that will help him navigate past the healthy brain to remove the tumour,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.88,0:20:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,肿瘤显示为虚线.\N{\rasEng}which is shown as a dotted line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,经过了近五个小时的手术,肿瘤被成功摘除.\N{\rasEng}After nearly five hours of surgery,the tumour is finally removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.48,0:20:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是取出来的.\N{\rasEng}This is the specimen that's come out so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.12,0:20:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它在颞极前四厘米处,这是脑肿瘤的确切位置.\N{\rasEng}It's the front four centimetres of the temporal pole,which is exactly where the brain tumour is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.00,0:20:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我认为肿瘤就在这个位置,最底部的右侧.\N{\rasEng}I think the brain tumour is in this bit here,right at the very bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Elyse再次接受了扫描,确认已经没有脑肿瘤.\N{\rasEng}And then Elyse is scanned again to ensure that none of the tumour remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.28,0:21:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这张照片看起来不可思议.太神奇了.\N{\rasEng}The pictures look amazing. Fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.72,0:21:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,两个月后当Elyse过她18岁生日时我去拜访她.\N{\rasEng}Two months later and I'm off to visit Elyse on her 18th birthday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.04,0:21:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,你好,生日快乐！这是送给你的花.\N{\rasEng}Hello. Happy birthday. There's some flowers for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.88,0:21:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴地看到,她完全康复了.\N{\rasEng}I'm delighted to see that she's made a full recovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.80,0:21:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,令人惊讶的是,就在手术前几个星期,她曾一天里发作多达8次.\N{\rasEng}It's amazing that only a few weeks ago before the operation,she was having up to eight seizures a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.84,0:21:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你现在还有任何发作吗？\N{\rasEng}Are you having any seizures at all？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.96,0:21:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- 没有.- 那这确实改变了你的生活？\N{\rasEng}None. So it's really changed your life？
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.32,0:21:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,是的.\N{\rasEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.28,0:21:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这太不可思议了！\N{\rasEng}That's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.20,0:21:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,外科医生的技能和MRI技术的奇妙结合\N{\rasEng}It's miraculous to see how the surgeons' skill and MRI technology
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.72,0:21:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,已经完全改变了Elyse的生活.\N{\rasEng}has totally transformed Elyse's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.00,0:21:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在过去50年创新、发明和发现以前所未有的规模出现.\N{\rasEng}The past 50 years has seen innovation,invention and discovery on an unprecedented scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.68,0:22:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我选择我认为是最好的,过去半个世纪里的十大科学进展.\N{\rasEng}I'm choosing what I think are the very best,the top ten scientific advances of the past half century.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.48,0:22:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,到目前为止,我们已经看到了避孕药对妇女\N{\rasEng}So far we've seen how the pill has revolutionised women's
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.36,0:22:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至每个人的生活产生的重大影响.\N{\rasEng}and indeed everybody's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.32,0:22:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经或多或少看了微芯片在应用上的神奇作用\N{\rasEng}We've looked at the almost miraculous effect of the microchip on,well,more or less everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.44,0:22:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,透过 MRI 扫描,我们可以一窥令人惊奇的大脑的神奇能力\N{\rasEng}and we've marvelled at our godlike ability to peer into the mind,thanks to MRI scanning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.40,0:22:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,接下来还有七个科学进步.\N{\rasEng}There are still seven of my top ten to come
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.44,0:22:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在节目的最后,你有机会选出你最喜欢的科学进步.\N{\rasEng}and after the programme,you'll get a chance to vote on which is your favourite,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.24,0:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,最棒中的最棒\N{\rasEng}the best of the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,与此同时,在这个名单中\N{\rasEng}Meanwhile,on with the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.88,0:22:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我的第四个选择,虽然相当熟悉,但有可能拯救地球.\N{\rasEng}My fourth choice,which though rather familiar,has the potential to save the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.52,0:22:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,我当然不会把它排除在外.\N{\rasEng}I certainly wouldn't be without this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我最喜欢的发明之一.电筒\N{\rasEng}It's one of my favourite inventions. It's the electric torch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.00,0:23:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但光的应用发展的重大进步\N{\rasEng}But the great advance in the use of light came 50 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.88,0:23:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,是在50年前发明了激光,把光线集中在一个非常小的区域内,非常精确.\N{\rasEng}with the invention of the laser,which concentrates the light down a very narrow beam,very precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.00,0:23:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这是自从人类点亮第一支蜡烛以来,光学的最重大进步.\N{\rasEng}It's the greatest advance in the technology of light since mankind lit its first candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.40,0:23:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,一束激光产生的光线如此集中,以至于它可以用来点火、切割和摧毁.\N{\rasEng}A laser produces light that's so concentrated it can burn,cut and destroy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.36,0:23:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,从一开始,这个破坏力\N{\rasEng}From the very beginning,this destructive power
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.76,0:23:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,引发了人科幻作家的想象力.\N{\rasEng}has sparked the imagination of science fiction writers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.40,0:23:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,他选择了自己的死亡！\N{\rasEng}He has chosen his own death!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.76,0:23:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这种力量也可以用来做有益的事,这就是为什么它在我的十大科学进步名单中.\N{\rasEng}But the force can also be used for good and that's why it's in my top ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.76,0:23:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是功率为1瓦的激光.\N{\rasEng}Here's a laser of a power of one watt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.04,0:23:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你不想自己划亮火柴,你可以把它放在这束光里.\N{\rasEng}If you don't want to use your energy to strike your match,you can just hold it in the beam of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.72,0:24:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,一束1瓦的激光可以点燃火柴.\N{\rasEng}A one-watt laser can light a match.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.80,0:24:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,想象一下\N{\rasEng}Imagine,then,the power
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.84,0:24:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,500万亿瓦激光.\N{\rasEng}of a 500 trillion watt laser.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.60,0:24:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这正是他们建在加利福尼亚州国家点火中心的装置\N{\rasEng}That's exactly what they've built here at the National Ignition Facility in California,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.00,0:24:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,在那儿,工程师们刚刚建完世界上最强大的激光.\N{\rasEng}where engineers have just finishing constructing the laser to end all lasers.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.12,0:24:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上,192束世界上功率最大的激光\N{\rasEng}In fact,192 of the world's most powerful lasers,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.20,0:24:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,聚焦在氢原子上.\N{\rasEng}all focused on a tiny hydrogen target.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.08,0:24:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,如果它们能在同一时间照射目标\N{\rasEng}If they can be made to strike at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.88,0:24:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我所说的同一时间是十亿分之一秒,\N{\rasEng}and when I say the same time,I mean within one billionth of a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.28,0:24:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这时原子中的能量就会被释放出来\N{\rasEng}then the energy inside the atoms will be released,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.12,0:24:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,释放出超过整个美国国家电网\N{\rasEng}creating in one moment 500 times more energy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.88,0:24:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,500倍的能量.\N{\rasEng}than the entire American National Grid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.44,0:24:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这不可思议的能量来自核聚变\N{\rasEng}This incredible energy release is from nuclear fusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.16,0:25:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,什么是核聚变能量？核聚变能量就是太阳内部的能量来源.\N{\rasEng}What is fusion power？ Fusion power is what's going on inside the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.80,0:25:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,当我们把氢原子聚合到一起,就会发生核聚变,\N{\rasEng}When we crush hydrogen together,we get this fusion to happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.64,0:25:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把物质转化成能量\N{\rasEng}we turn mass into energy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.32,0:25:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,能量释放出来,如果我们收集这些能量.\N{\rasEng}and that energy comes out and if we can collect it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.64,0:25:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,把它转换为电能,驱动我们文明的能源.这就是核聚变能量.\N{\rasEng}and turn it into electricity,that's what we want to power our civilization. That's fusion power.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.60,0:25:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们希望在这个靶室发生的.\N{\rasEng}That's what we hope to make happen in this target chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.52,0:25:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这种能源让人激动的是没有污染问题\N{\rasEng}What is so exciting about this energy,we have no issue of pollution
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.04,0:25:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,不会造成全球变暖.\N{\rasEng}and we have no issue of global climate warming.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.60,0:25:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我们的梦想.充满梦想和希望的核聚变发电,\N{\rasEng}That is the dream. That has always been the dream of fusion energy
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.68,0:25:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- 在这里我们将会实现它.- 没有核废物？\N{\rasEng}and hopefully,we'll be able to do it here. And no nuclear waste？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.20,0:25:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,对,没有核废物.\N{\rasEng}No nuclear waste. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.96,0:25:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道这套装置的未来几年内\N{\rasEng}I just know that in this facility in the next couple of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.48,0:25:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,有望找到解决之道.\N{\rasEng}hopefully one,we will find out that we can do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.04,0:25:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上,在这个实验室里Ed和他的同事\N{\rasEng}Effectively,within this chamber,Ed and his colleagues
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.80,0:25:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,尝试创造并捕获这种恒星的能量\N{\rasEng}are trying to create and capture the power of a star
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.48,0:26:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,将原子聚合成质子.\N{\rasEng}by fusing protons in an atom.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.40,0:26:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,如此强大的能量来源,如果它可以被开发利用,\N{\rasEng}A source of energy so powerful that if it could be harnessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.28,0:26:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,将提供更便宜,更清洁的可再生能源\N{\rasEng}it would provide the Holy Grail of cheaper,cleaner renewable energy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.92,0:26:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,并减少对化石燃料的依赖.\N{\rasEng}and reduce our dependence on fossil fuels.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.48,0:26:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,不同寻常的是这台庞大的装置\N{\rasEng}What's utterly extraordinary is that all this energy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.16,0:26:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,产生的所有能量都来自那里.\N{\rasEng}that you're generating from this vast machine is actually in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.44,0:26:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,让我看看那个小小的胶囊.\N{\rasEng}Just show me that little capsule.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.24,0:26:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这胶囊就是存储氢燃料的地方.\N{\rasEng}That capsule is where the hydrogen fuel resides.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.68,0:26:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,氢在这里处于接近绝对零度的状态,激光照射进来并加热它.\N{\rasEng}It resides there at near absolute zero and the laser light comes in and it heats up this can.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.48,0:26:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,当外壳炸开时氢原子被加速到每小时150万公里\N{\rasEng}When the shell explodes,that hydrogen implodes at nearly 1.5 million kilometres per hour
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.16,0:26:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是我们制造核聚变的方法.\N{\rasEng}and that's how we get that fusion to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.52,0:27:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这种使用激光的想法不仅解决物理学的一大难题\N{\rasEng}The idea of using the laser to solve one of the great problems of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.12,0:27:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,还可以生产清洁能源,有可能会拯救我们的星球.\N{\rasEng}the production of green energy,which might save the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.76,0:27:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,利用核聚变.这似乎是一个发展激光器的非常重要的原因.\N{\rasEng}using nuclear fusion. That seems to be a really important reason for developing lasers.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.12,0:27:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,有趣的是当发明激光时\N{\rasEng}It's interesting to remember that when lasers were invented,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.68,0:27:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,没人能想象到激光会有这么多用途.\N{\rasEng}no-one imagined how many uses we'd have for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.16,0:27:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,很不幸,但事实是战争会促使我们在某些方面取得重大进展.\N{\rasEng}It's unfortunate but true that war is when we make some of our greatest advances.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.04,0:27:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我的下一条就复杂得多.\N{\rasEng}And my next owes much to conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.96,0:27:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我是晚上在阿富汗南部巡逻时踩到一个简易爆炸装置.\N{\rasEng}I was in southern Afghanistan on patrol at night and stepped on an IED.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.00,0:27:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我还记得看到了一片闪光,然后感觉被抛到了半空中又摔下来,\N{\rasEng}I remember seeing the flash,the feeling of going through the air,landing,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.56,0:28:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,距我15英尺的同伴被炸死.\N{\rasEng}and I got blown about 15 feet away from the lads.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.88,0:28:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,我立刻明白发生了什么,马上检查自己\N{\rasEng}I knew what happened straightaway cos I checked myself
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.32,0:28:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,看看我的手指、我的手还在不在.\N{\rasEng}to see if I had all my fingers,my hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.16,0:28:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我一摸我的腿,“它不在了,够公平的”我想.\N{\rasEng}I got to my leg,and I thought,"That ain't there. Fair enough."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.60,0:28:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我检查另一条腿,它严重出血.\N{\rasEng}I checked the other leg and that was bleeding badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.68,0:28:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,骨头和其他的东西全碎了,我想等我再醒来时这条腿就没了.\N{\rasEng}All shattered bones and everything else,so I knew that probably wouldn't be there when I woke up.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.48,0:28:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,该你了.\N{\rasEng}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.48,0:28:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,直到前不久,Sam 都在也不能站起来走路,\N{\rasEng}Until recently,Sam would have never walked again,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.96,0:28:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但是现在生物力学科学在模仿我们身体的\N{\rasEng}but now the science of biomechanics is getting closer than ever before
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.64,0:28:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,复杂性和精密度上都比以前有了更大进展.\N{\rasEng}to mimicking the complexity and sophistication of our own bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.84,0:28:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,在 Headley Court 军队康复中心,\N{\rasEng}At Headley Court Military Rehabilitation Centre,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.56,0:28:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,医生正在帮助数百名像Sam这样受伤的士兵.\N{\rasEng}doctors are helping hundreds of injured soldiers like Sam.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.44,0:28:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Sam,你什么时候受的伤？\N{\rasEng}Sam,when were you injured？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.24,0:28:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,八月初.\N{\rasEng}Beginning of August.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.12,0:28:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,现在你已经能够行走了？\N{\rasEng}So you're already walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.48,0:28:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是？5个月？\N{\rasEng}So that's what？ Five months？
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.96,0:29:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,- 对,是的.- 这是相当了不起. - 是啊.\N{\rasEng}About that,yeah. Which is rather impressive. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.28,0:29:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你的一个巨大努力？ 想必这一定是.\N{\rasEng}Has that been a massive effort for you？ Presumably,it must have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.60,0:29:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,确实充满挑战.一直想超过和我类似情况的朋友.\N{\rasEng}More of a challenge,really. Been trying to beat some Para friends of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.92,0:29:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,你在不断的挑战你自己？\N{\rasEng}Do you compete amongst yourselves？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.68,0:29:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我们之间有很多竞争,看谁最先离开这儿.\N{\rasEng}There's a lot of competition between us to see who can be out quickest.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.80,0:29:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- 作为士兵你更有竞争力.- 肯定\N{\rasEng}Being soldiers,you tend to be competitive. Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.60,0:29:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,令人惊奇的是Sam的假肢是由电脑控制的.\N{\rasEng}The amazing thing about Sam's artificial legs is that they're controlled by a computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.72,0:29:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,电脑在哪儿？\N{\rasEng}Where is the computer in this？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.76,0:29:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在膝关节的后面.\N{\rasEng}It's just behind the knee joint.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.00,0:29:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,在胫骨安装了一些传感器,\N{\rasEng}In the shin we've got some strain gauges
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.68,0:29:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这些传感器每秒发送50次数据给电脑,来调节液压系统.\N{\rasEng}and they give 50 readings per second back to the computer,which then regulates the hydraulics.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.20,0:29:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这真的能让这个人工膝盖能如此稳定的正常行走.\N{\rasEng}That's really what makes this knee so stable in normal walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.12,0:29:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在这之前,失去双腿对Sam造成了怎样的影响？\N{\rasEng}In the early days,an injury would have resulted in what for Sam？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.52,0:29:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他一生的大部分时间可能都得坐在轮椅上.\N{\rasEng}He'd have probably been sat in a wheelchair for most of his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.60,0:29:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,现在,他花费几乎所有的时间在他的双腿,走路.\N{\rasEng}Now he spends pretty much all his time on his legs,walking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.32,0:29:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- 所以这改变了他的生活？- 绝对是.\N{\rasEng}So it's life-changing？ Absolutely. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.84,0:30:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,现在没有任何事你不能做,就像你过去那样.\N{\rasEng}There isn't anything that you can't do now that you used to be able to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.36,0:30:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,滑雪,游泳,跑步,骑自行车.\N{\rasEng}Skiing,swimming,running,going on the bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.16,0:30:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,你期望回到滑雪场？当然可以.\N{\rasEng}You'd expect to get back on the ski slopes？ Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.84,0:30:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你有正确的东西,正确的态度,\N{\rasEng}If you've got the right stuff,the right attitude,you can pretty much carry on with everything
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.78,0:30:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,你几乎可以像以前那样做任何事情.没有东西能阻止你.\N{\rasEng}as good as before. Nothing stopping you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.00,0:30:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅受伤的士兵可以从新技术中获益.\N{\rasEng}And it is isn't only wounded soldiers that are benefiting from this new technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.24,0:30:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,从头部到脚趾,生物力学是设法修理和更换大自然的精心调校的“机器”.\N{\rasEng}From head to toe,biomechanics is finding ways to repair and replace nature's finely-tuned machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.96,0:30:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,生物力学的雄心是制造要真正的一体化假肢.\N{\rasEng}The ambition for biomechanics is for prosthetics to be truly integrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.24,0:30:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,为达成这个目标,研究者需要收集使用者的想法.\N{\rasEng}And for that,they would need to be controlled by the user's mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.08,0:30:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是直到前不久,介入大脑同步工作还是无法实现的.\N{\rasEng}But until recently,interfering with the workings of the brain just wasn't an option.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.80,0:30:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,但是今天,这开始有了变化\N{\rasEng}But today,that's all starting to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.04,0:30:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,深入研究和操作大脑的能力有许多潜在的好处,\N{\rasEng}The ability to delve into and manipulate the brain has
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.80,0:31:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,而不只是控制假肢.\N{\rasEng}many potential benefits,not only for the control of prosthetic limbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.04,0:31:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Diane Hire 患有抑郁症超过20年.\N{\rasEng}Diane Hire suffered from depression for more than 20 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.92,0:31:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,她的病是如此严重,它甚至驱使她试图三次自杀.\N{\rasEng}Her illness was so crippling that it even drove her to attempt suicide three times.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.48,0:31:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,告诉我很沮丧是什么感觉.\N{\rasEng}So tell me what it's like to be depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.68,0:31:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,它很可怕,就像身处一个黑暗的洞穴里.\N{\rasEng}It's awful,it's like being in a dark cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.52,0:31:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,周围没有人,孤独、寒冷.\N{\rasEng}Nobody around,cold,lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.32,0:31:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你有抑郁症,你绝对没有活下去的愿望.\N{\rasEng}If you have depression,you have absolutely no desire to live
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.32,0:31:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,就是这样,日复一日\N{\rasEng}and it just is like that day after day after day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.16,0:31:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,其实,我想我从中感觉到了死亡\N{\rasEng}Actually,I guess I felt dead inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.24,0:31:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,我就像一个活着,却谈论死亡的人.\N{\rasEng}I was like a living,talking dead person.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.44,0:31:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我尝试过几种药,我也试过ECT治疗,电休克治疗.\N{\rasEng}I tried several medications and I also tried ECT,electroconvulsive therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.76,0:31:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,那些同样可怕\N{\rasEng}That was pretty awful too!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.40,0:31:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,还有最后一种手段来尝试控制她的抑郁症,Diane接受了一项\N{\rasEng}In a last-ditch attempt to control her depression,Diane underwent
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.44,0:32:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,开创性的手术,希望由此控制自己的灾难性抑郁症.\N{\rasEng}groundbreaking surgery in the hope of controlling her devastating depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.16,0:32:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,经过5小时的手术,电极植入了她大脑内8厘米深的地方.\N{\rasEng}In a five-hour operation,electrodes were directly inserted eight centimetres into her brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.48,0:32:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,为了测试电极位置是否正确,Diane在手术中醒来\N{\rasEng}To check the electrodes were in the correct position,Diane was woken up
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.36,0:32:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,以便调整电脉冲.\N{\rasEng}during the procedure,so that the impulses could be adjusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.40,0:32:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道,当我醒来,他们说,\N{\rasEng}You know,when I woke up,they said,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.56,0:32:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"我们现在将打开它,你要告诉我们你的感觉."\N{\rasEng}"We're going to turn this on now and you let us know how things are feeling."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.96,0:32:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我头一次感到无法形容的温暖,然后他们调到另外一个设置,我的心开始飞舞.\N{\rasEng}And at first I felt pretty warm,and then they turned it to another setting,and my heart was galloping.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.80,0:32:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你感觉如何？笑一个.\N{\rasEng}How you feeling？ Starting to smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.28,0:32:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我感觉很快乐.然后我脸上出现了一个大大的笑容.\N{\rasEng}I feel happy. Then all of a sudden,I got this great big grin on my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.20,0:32:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,之后,他们让我重新入睡\N{\rasEng}And after that,they put me back to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.16,0:32:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,以便结束手术.\N{\rasEng}to finish up the surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.24,0:32:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,你突然间就感觉到快乐？\N{\rasEng}So you immediately felt happy suddenly？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.28,0:32:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,是的,立刻,对于我来说,那像什么？\N{\rasEng}Oh yes,for me it was instantaneous. What was that like？
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.92,0:32:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,不可思议\N{\rasEng}Amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.52,0:32:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,就像我的大脑在做体操.\N{\rasEng}It was almost like my brain was doing gymnastics.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.24,0:33:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,这就像我以前去上班时的感觉,你知道.\N{\rasEng}You know it's how I used to feel when I would go to work
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.08,0:33:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,还有……\N{\rasEng}and...and...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.88,0:33:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,在一个美好的周末,做一些好的事情.\N{\rasEng}you know,have good weekends and do things.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Diane和这个连接在她身体上,像心脏起搏器一样的系统共同生活了三年\N{\rasEng}Three years later and Diane lives with the system wired into her own body,much like a pacemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.96,0:33:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,它安装在哪儿？\N{\rasEng}And where do the wires run？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.44,0:33:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,控制器在你的胸部,是吗？\N{\rasEng}The control box is in your chest,isn't it？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.08,0:33:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是的.从这儿开始然后,顺着我脑袋后面\N{\rasEng}Right. They start here,and then they go down the back of my skull,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.56,0:33:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,再到我的脖子后面,绕一圈\N{\rasEng}down the back of my neck and around and plug into
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.40,0:33:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,然后插入我胸部的电池盒.\N{\rasEng}a battery pack on my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.72,0:33:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,你担心过一个完全处于试验阶段的设备,安装在你脑袋里吗？\N{\rasEng}Does it worry you that you have a totally experimental thing inside your brain？
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.12,0:33:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,不,不,因为这很值得.\N{\rasEng}No. No,because it's been worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.36,0:33:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,每当电脉冲释放一次,Diane的抑郁症就消失了.\N{\rasEng}From the very moment the electrodes were switched on,Diane's depression disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.60,0:34:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,当然,你的生活就彻底改变了.\N{\rasEng}And of course your life has changed totally.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.36,0:34:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,180度\N{\rasEng}180 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.40,0:34:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,每天早上我醒来,我就想"今天我要处于什么状态？"\N{\rasEng}I wake up every day,and I think,"What's today going to bring？"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.48,0:34:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我对生活有着从来不曾有过的激情.\N{\rasEng}I have an excitement about living that I didn't ever have.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.28,0:34:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,所以你是完美的仿生的女人？\N{\rasEng}So you're the perfect bionic woman？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.36,0:34:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,是的,是的.\N{\rasEng}Yeah. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.04,0:34:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,即使作为最后手段,将电子设备插入大脑中心深处的方式,\N{\rasEng}Even as a last resort,it seems utterly terrifying to think of
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.28,0:34:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这种想法看上去似乎十分可怕,可是这就是Diane身上发生的.\N{\rasEng}thrusting an electronic device deep into the centre of the brain in the way that has happened with Diane.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.56,0:34:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但你不能挑剔它,因为它完全改变了她的生活.\N{\rasEng}But you can't knock it,because it's completely changed her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.96,0:34:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,因为它改变生命和触及很多其他方面的能力,\N{\rasEng}Because of its power to transform lives and potential to touch many others,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.40,0:34:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,仿生学肯定在我的榜单中.\N{\rasEng}bionics definitely has a place in my top ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.04,0:34:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,这是不是过去50年来最重大的进步？\N{\rasEng}Is it the most significant advance of the last 50 years？
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.64,0:34:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这由你在节目的末尾来决定.\N{\rasEng}That's up to you to decide at the end of the programme.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.20,0:34:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,或者你再看看我的下一个选择 - 一个了不起的发明\N{\rasEng}Or maybe you'll go for my next choice - a remarkable invention
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.68,0:35:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,超越其他所有的,也许,能导致改变.\N{\rasEng}that more than any other,perhaps,has caused change.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.24,0:35:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,它改变了我工作的方式.\N{\rasEng}It's changed the way I work.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.88,0:35:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,它改变了我的发现新的艺术的方式.\N{\rasEng}It's changed the way I find out about new art.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.84,0:35:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,跟踪我的孩子在做什么.\N{\rasEng}Keep track of what my kids are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.12,0:35:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,比较价格.查一查足球比分.\N{\rasEng}Compare prices. Look up football scores.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.20,0:35:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,和朋友交谈.和女孩们聊天!\N{\rasEng}Talk to friends. Chat up girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.80,0:35:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,为慈善事业筹集资金.看新闻\N{\rasEng}Raise money for charity. Watch the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.40,0:35:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它改变了研究的方式.\N{\rasEng}It's changed the way I do my research.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.24,0:35:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上,它通过无数种方式改变了我们的生活.\N{\rasEng}In fact,it's changed our lives in a thousand ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.76,0:35:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我,其中之一,也不能独善其身.\N{\rasEng}I,for one,couldn't do without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.88,0:35:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它就是互联网！\N{\rasEng}It is,of course,the World Wide Web!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.08,0:35:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,想到我们大多数人第一次上线是在十年前,就让人觉得很吃惊.\N{\rasEng}It's astonishing to think that the majority of us went on-line for the very first time just ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.68,0:35:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我第一次联上互联网是我在实验室\N{\rasEng}My first contact with the Internet was one day when I went into the lab
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.68,0:35:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,看我的中国博士研究生在她的屏幕上打字.\N{\rasEng}and saw my Chinese PhD student typing on her screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.44,0:35:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,她在那儿打字,\N{\rasEng}And there she was,typing,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.96,0:35:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,突然她的手离开了键盘.\N{\rasEng}and then suddenly she took her hands off the keyboard
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.00,0:36:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在屏幕下方出现了一些字符.\N{\rasEng}and some other letters appeared just underneath.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.84,0:36:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,她和香港的某个人在交流.\N{\rasEng}She was communicating with somebody in Hong Kong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.68,0:36:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我想,"这绝不会过时"\N{\rasEng}I thought,"This will never take off!"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.76,0:36:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,互联网要求世界上所有的电脑\N{\rasEng}The World Wide Web required all the computers in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.80,0:36:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,使用同一种语言,以便能够相互交流.\N{\rasEng}to be able to talk to each other using one common language.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.20,0:36:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但是直到1990年之前这都不可能,一个名叫Tim Berners-Lee的英国科学家\N{\rasEng}But that was impossible until 1990,when a British scientist called Tim Berners-Lee
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.84,0:36:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,只出了一种连接所有人的方法.\N{\rasEng}figured out a way to link everybody up.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.96,0:36:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,# Welcome to my world... #\N{\rasEng}# Welcome to my world... #
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.36,0:36:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,他创造了一种代码让所有人可以交流.\N{\rasEng}He created a code allowing computers to share information.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.36,0:36:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,一夜之间,我们就可以相互交流了.\N{\rasEng}And suddenly,we could speak to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.20,0:36:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,# Welcome to my world... #\N{\rasEng}# Welcome to my world... #
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.20,0:36:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,一个新的信息交流时代开始了.\N{\rasEng}And a new age of communications began.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.84,0:36:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,# Built with you in mind... #\N{\rasEng}# Built with you in mind... #
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.32,0:36:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,由于网络从来没有申请专利,所以它是免费和开放给任何人使用.\N{\rasEng}Because the Web was never patented,it is free and open to anyone to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.44,0:36:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,如今全球范围内有1.7亿人使用互联网.\N{\rasEng}Today,1.7 billion people use the web globally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.80,0:37:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,嗨大家好,今天我们要做一个好莱坞的嘴唇看.\N{\rasEng}Hi,everyone,today we're going to be doing a Hollywood lip look.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.36,0:37:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当你打算煮蛋却没有煮蛋器时,那就麻烦了.\N{\rasEng}When you're poaching eggs without an egg poacher,it can get messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.80,0:37:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你能像这样跳舞...\N{\rasEng}So if you can dance like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.44,0:37:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,自从印刷术发明以来我们就没有见过这样的飞跃,\N{\rasEng}Not since the invention of the printing press
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.88,0:37:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,如此大量的信息给所有人免费使用.\N{\rasEng}have we seen such a leap forward in the amount of information freely available to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.24,0:37:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,而以前从未有过这样一个平台让普通人发出他们的声音.\N{\rasEng}And never before has there been such a platform for ordinary people to make their voices heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.64,0:37:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,这只是我的意见,你不同意,无所谓！\N{\rasEng}This is just my opinion,you disagree,feel free!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.56,0:37:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这是我们和朋友交流的方式.\N{\rasEng}It's how we communicate with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.68,0:37:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们中的一亿人使用社交网站\N{\rasEng}One billion of us using social networking sites
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.24,0:37:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,还有三百万人在虚拟世界碰面.\N{\rasEng}and 300 million meet people in a virtual world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.72,0:37:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的孩子用它来进行互动,学习和玩耍.\N{\rasEng}Our children use it to interact,to learn and play.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.24,0:37:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,它改变了新闻和信息.\N{\rasEng}It's transformed news and information.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.68,0:37:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在商业上,我们都变成商人,买卖东西只需点击一个按钮.\N{\rasEng}In business,we've all become traders,buying and selling at the click of a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.92,0:37:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,对于接触暴力和色情的这些风险,令人担忧的问题我们必须面对,\N{\rasEng}For all the risk of exposure to violence and pornography,worrying issues we have to face,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.12,0:38:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,互联网是过去50年来最重大的进步之一.\N{\rasEng}the Internet is one of the most significant advances of the past 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.24,0:38:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说,网络是非常令人振奋,\N{\rasEng}And for me,the Web is exciting,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.12,0:38:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,因为它允许我们以前所未有的方式参与到科学研究中.\N{\rasEng}because it allows all of us to participate in science like never before.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.16,0:38:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Chris Lintott博士的工作是对来自\N{\rasEng}Dr Chris Lintott has the task of classifying
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.72,0:38:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,机器人望远镜照片中上百万个星系进行分类.\N{\rasEng}over a million galaxies from photos taken by robotic telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.28,0:38:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这些数据量让他不堪重负,他聘请了数千名网上志愿者来帮助他.\N{\rasEng}He was so overwhelmed by the amount of data that he enlisted thousands of on-line volunteers to help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.12,0:38:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但真正令人兴奋的是,这些扶手椅上的科学家的新发现.\N{\rasEng}But the really exciting thing is that these armchair scientists made a new discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.80,0:38:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,几年前,一组志愿者注意到\N{\rasEng}A couple of years ago,a group of our volunteers noticed that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.80,0:38:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,在一些图像的背景上有一些小的、圆的、绿色的点.\N{\rasEng}in the background of some of the images,there were these small,round,green objects.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.24,0:38:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,他们称之为豌豆.志愿者们发现它们有数百个之多,"这都是些什么？"\N{\rasEng}They called them peas. They found a couple of hundred of them and said,"What are these？"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.68,0:38:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,通过一些世界上最大的望远镜我们观测了它们.\N{\rasEng}We've looked at these with some of the world's largest telescopes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:38:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它们是星系中的恒星经过剧烈爆发形成的.\N{\rasEng}They are galaxies undergoing a dramatic burst of star formation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.00,0:39:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这是宇宙中制造恒星最有效的方式.\N{\rasEng}These are the most efficient makers of stars anywhere in the local universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.36,0:39:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,它们被专业的天文学家忽略了.\N{\rasEng}They'd been missed by professional astronomers.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.04,0:39:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,这要感谢上百万人,他们的扶手椅\N{\rasEng}It was only thanks to a quarter of a million people,their armchairs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.72,0:39:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,和他们的网络连接,让我们发现了这些\N{\rasEng}and their Internet connections that they came to our attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.20,0:39:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,星系动物园,只是一个邀请公众参与科学研究的项目服务器之一\N{\rasEng}Galaxy Zoo is just one of a host of projects inviting the public to get involved in science.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.28,0:39:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,又有谁能知道互联网把这样的合作变为可能,\N{\rasEng}Who knows what progress we could make through
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.64,0:39:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,通过这种合作我们又能取得什么样的进展？\N{\rasEng}collaborations like these,made possible by the Internet？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.88,0:39:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这是人类信息交流的\N{\rasEng}This massive progress
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.68,0:39:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,巨大进步\N{\rasEng}in how humans exchange information
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.96,0:39:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,毫无疑问这是过去50年取得的一个决定性的进步\N{\rasEng}undoubtedly makes it one of the defining advances in the last 50 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.36,0:39:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,互联网对我们生活产生的深远影响\N{\rasEng}Does the far-reaching impact of the World Wide Web on all our lives
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.72,0:39:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,是否使它成为最重要的进步？\N{\rasEng}make it the most significant advance？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.84,0:39:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,或者革命性的人机互联意味着仿生学会赢得你的投票？\N{\rasEng}Or does the revolutionary joining of man with machine mean that biomechanics gets your vote？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.84,0:40:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,如假包换的清洁能源会让激光成为你心目中的第一名？\N{\rasEng}Could it be the promise of clean energy for us all that makes the laser your number one？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.96,0:40:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你决定之前还有四个科学进步可以考虑.\N{\rasEng}Before you decide,there are four more advances to consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.44,0:40:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,下一个有可能改变我们所相信的一切.\N{\rasEng}The next one has the potential to change everything we've ever believed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.36,0:40:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,是什么让我们区别于其它动物呢？\N{\rasEng}What distinguishes us from all other creatures？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.56,0:40:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,是人类的探索精神.\N{\rasEng}It's human inquisitiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.24,0:40:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我们为什么在这里？ 我们会去哪里？\N{\rasEng}Why are we here？ Where are we going？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.24,0:40:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们在宇宙的什么位置？\N{\rasEng}What's our place in the universe？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.20,0:40:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,从天上俯瞰我们的这个世界,你会意识到我们有多么渺小.\N{\rasEng}Looking down on the world from above,you realise just how insignificant we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.44,0:40:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,自从时间诞生,人们惊奇于\N{\rasEng}Since the dawn of time,people have marvelled
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.44,0:40:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们周围的辽阔并惊奇,"这些是如何开始的？"\N{\rasEng}at the vastness around us and wondered,"How did it all begin？"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.08,0:41:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,在20世纪20年代,美国科学家Edwin Hubble\N{\rasEng}In the 1920s,American astronomer Edwin Hubble
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.52,0:41:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,发现了宇宙在膨胀,\N{\rasEng}showed that the universe was expanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.36,0:41:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,基于这样一个简单的观测,\N{\rasEng}and from this simple observation,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.60,0:41:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你将时间倒流,通过计算\N{\rasEng}it was calculated that if you run the clock back...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.40,0:41:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的一切都诞生于140亿年前的一次大爆炸.\N{\rasEng}..everything must have exploded into existence nearly 14 billion years ago in a big bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.32,0:41:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,对于我,一想到大爆炸这个充满想象力的想法,就感到激动.\N{\rasEng}For me,I suppose what I find so exciting about big bang is the ambition of the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.20,0:41:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,现在有一种想法,不仅仅关于我们的星球或我们的太阳系\N{\rasEng}Here is an idea that is not just about our planet or our solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.56,0:41:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,而是统一我们对于整个宇宙的看法.\N{\rasEng}but unifies our whole notion of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它将告诉关于我们的起源,我们从哪儿来,还有可能回答我们会到哪儿去.\N{\rasEng}And it tells us about our beginnings,about where we came from and possibly to where we are going.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.24,0:41:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,不过大爆炸理论还预言整个宇宙\N{\rasEng}But the big-bang theory also predicted that the entire universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.24,0:42:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的行星和星系,我们周围所看到的,来自于无.\N{\rasEng}all the planets and galaxies we see around us,exploded from nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.36,0:42:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,听起来很疯狂\N{\rasEng}Which sounds crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.00,0:42:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,当差不多100年前它首次提出时,这种想法还充满争议,\N{\rasEng}When it was first proposed almost 100 years ago,the idea was controversial,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.68,0:42:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,但在过去50年中,科学已经开始收集到确凿的证据\N{\rasEng}but in the last 50 years,science has started to gather hard evidence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.92,0:42:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,来证明大爆炸很可能不是一个疯狂的想法.\N{\rasEng}that the big bang might not be such a crazy idea after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.04,0:42:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,1965年,两个在新泽西州卫星天线工作的\N{\rasEng}In 1965,two radio astronomers working on this satellite antenna
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.28,0:42:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,射电天文学家始终会接收到一个奇怪的信号.\N{\rasEng}in New Jersey started to pick up a strange signal.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.96,0:42:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这个无线电信号来自宇宙深空\N{\rasEng}This radiation was coming from somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.12,0:42:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,的任何方向.\N{\rasEng}in really deep cosmic space,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.44,0:42:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,超过了我们任何已知的广播信号源\N{\rasEng}beyond any radio sources that any of us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.24,0:42:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是幻想中的.\N{\rasEng}knew about or even dreamed existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.56,0:42:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,这种辐射的大胆解释是它也许是\N{\rasEng}The daring explanation for the radiation was that it might be
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.36,0:42:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,大爆炸的最后遗迹回响在时间和空间里.\N{\rasEng}the last remnant of the big bang echoing through space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.84,0:42:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,也许\N{\rasEng}Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.12,0:42:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,2001年,WMAP探测器分析了这种辐射\N{\rasEng}In 2001,the WMAP spacecraft analysed this radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.60,0:42:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,据此还绘制了一幅宇宙早期的图像\N{\rasEng}and even produced a map of the early universe
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.88,0:43:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,那看上去或多或少支持了大爆炸理论.\N{\rasEng}that seemed to more or less prove the big-bang theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.12,0:43:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但是遗憾的是,到目前为止,它并没有解释大爆炸发生的地方\N{\rasEng}But unfortunately,as yet,it doesn't explain why the big bang banged in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.12,0:43:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Lick天文台位于加州的高山上,天文学家正在试图计算宇宙膨胀的速度\N{\rasEng}High in the Californian hills at Lick Observatory,astronomers are trying to calculate
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.12,0:43:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们希望能够揭示一些光的问题.\N{\rasEng}how fast the universe is expanding,in the hope that they will be able shed some light on the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.80,0:43:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,并在这样做,他们有了一个惊人的发现.\N{\rasEng}And in doing so,they've made a surprising discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.84,0:43:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,人们预测引力会减慢\N{\rasEng}Everyone anticipated that gravity would slow down
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.80,0:43:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙膨胀的速度.\N{\rasEng}the expansion of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.68,0:43:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,因此我们试图测量宇宙在多大程度上减缓\N{\rasEng}So we were trying to measure how much the universe has been slowing down
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.48,0:43:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,以便预测是会一直膨胀下去,还是越来越慢,或重新收缩.\N{\rasEng}in order to predict whether it will expand forever,though more and more slowly or re-collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.80,0:43:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,相反,我们发现宇宙在加速膨胀.一点儿也没有减慢下来.\N{\rasEng}Instead,we found that it's actually speeding up. Not slowing down at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.56,0:43:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,一个加速中的宇宙\N{\rasEng}An accelerating universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.24,0:43:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,它如何工作？为什么要做那个？\N{\rasEng}How does that work？ Why should it do that？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.52,0:44:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们设想宇宙中充满了一种奇怪的东西,我们叫它暗能量,\N{\rasEng}Well,we think the universe is filled with some weird substance,we call it dark energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.12,0:44:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但实质上我们对它一无所知\N{\rasEng}but we know essentially nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.36,0:44:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,因此它的存在并在某种意义上,它是引力的反作用力\N{\rasEng}So it's there and in a sense,it's gravitationally repulsive,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.92,0:44:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,导致空间膨胀随时间越来越快.\N{\rasEng}causing space to expand faster and faster with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.24,0:44:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这些都在表明宇宙正在膨胀,\N{\rasEng}It's all very well to say the universe is expanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.00,0:44:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,但是有一个问题会让人们觉得迷惑,我们也膨胀吗？\N{\rasEng}but one of the questions that will puzzle a lot of people is,what are we expanding into？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.84,0:44:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,那实际上让我们都感到迷惑.\N{\rasEng}That actually puzzles all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.72,0:44:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可能会扩展到一个更大的超空间,一个有着更多维度的.\N{\rasEng}We may be expanding into a bigger hyperspace,one with more dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.28,0:44:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,在这个更大的空间中也许有着各种各样的宇宙.\N{\rasEng}And there could be all sorts of universes expanding within this bigger space.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.88,0:44:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的宇宙只是多元宇宙中的一个.\N{\rasEng}And ours is just one of these universes in the multiverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.36,0:44:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我接受你正在做的是难以置信的有趣,但也没用,是不是？\N{\rasEng}I accept that you're doing is incredibly interesting,but it's useless,isn't it？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.48,0:44:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,从某种意义上说,它是没用的,但是宇宙加速的性质是很重要的一部分\N{\rasEng}In a sense,it's useless,but the accelerating nature of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.12,0:44:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,因为它也许能帮助我们理解大爆炸.\N{\rasEng}is important in part because it may help us understand the big bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.16,0:44:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这是宇宙的诞生,\N{\rasEng}So it's the birth of the universe and so we should try to understand
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.28,0:44:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以试着理解它是如何发生的,宇宙从那时开始又是如何进化的.\N{\rasEng}how it is that it happened and how the universe has evolved since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.12,0:45:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但是,数据表明某些奇怪的,我相信,在这个阶段没有争议性.\N{\rasEng}But that the data are indicating something weird is,I believe,not controversial at this stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.84,0:45:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么大爆炸在我的科学进步名单中？\N{\rasEng}Why is big bang in my ten great ideas？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.16,0:45:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,它具有象征意义\N{\rasEng}Well,it's symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.44,0:45:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,它象征的一些我们人类独有的东西 -\N{\rasEng}It's symbolic of something that makes us uniquely human -
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.88,0:45:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的探索精神.\N{\rasEng}our inquisitiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.76,0:45:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,而这促使我们,通过科学,不断向前.\N{\rasEng}And it's that which drives us,through science,forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.36,0:45:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经大胆的踏入了外层空间,\N{\rasEng}We've had the audacity to tackle outer space,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.20,0:45:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们从没有进入过内部空间.\N{\rasEng}but we've had the nerve to take on inner space too.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.60,0:45:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我的最后三项科学进步都是关于我们自身...\N{\rasEng}My final three advances are all about understanding us...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.48,0:45:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,..源自一本2000年出版的书.\N{\rasEng}..starting with a remarkable book published in the year 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.60,0:46:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,115卷,就像这样\N{\rasEng}115 volumes like this
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.68,0:46:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,包含了一份完整的人类基因图,仅仅是一个人的.\N{\rasEng}contain the print-out of the human genome,from just one individual.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.00,0:46:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,30亿个字母.\N{\rasEng}Three billion letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.40,0:46:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,这是决定你是谁的配方.\N{\rasEng}It's the recipe for what makes you who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.68,0:46:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,这将彻底改变诊断、预防和大多数治疗方式,即便不是全部的人类的疾病\N{\rasEng}It will revolutionise the diagnosis,prevention and treatment of most,if not all,human diseases.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.20,0:46:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,十年前,破译人类基因组的工作\N{\rasEng}Ten years ago,decoding the human genome
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.92,0:46:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,的重要性被誉为就像把人送上月球,\N{\rasEng}was hailed by many as as significant as putting a man on the moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.28,0:46:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,是一个新千年希望的象征.\N{\rasEng}a symbol of the hope for the new millennium.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.12,0:46:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,所有期望的原因是 - 有人甚至认为是“炒作” -\N{\rasEng}The reason for all the hope - and some would even say "hype" -
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.48,0:46:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为基因治疗的巨大潜力.\N{\rasEng}was because of the enormous potential of gene therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.48,0:46:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,直到最近,医学也没有办法来恢复\N{\rasEng}Until recently,medicine could do nothing to restore
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.68,0:46:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,损坏或失灵的基因,但是今天,一些措施让我们看到了希望.\N{\rasEng}broken or malfunctioning genes,but today,there are some procedures which can offer hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.04,0:46:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,十来岁的Abdullahi准备做手术,可能改变他的遗传的命运.\N{\rasEng}Ten-year-old Abdullahi is about to undergo an operation which might change his genetic destiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.32,0:47:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Abdullahi视力差,尤其是夜视能力\N{\rasEng}Abdullahi has poor vision,particularly poor night vision,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.80,0:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,因为他缺乏的基因之一\N{\rasEng}because he lacks one of the genes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,转换成神经脉冲光能量不可或缺的.\N{\rasEng}essential for converting light energy into a nerve impulse,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.44,0:47:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,所以这次手术的目标是\N{\rasEng}so the idea of this operation
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.20,0:47:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,给他的视网膜提供一份该基因正确的、有功能的副本.\N{\rasEng}is to provide his retina with the correct,functioning copy of that gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.00,0:47:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,为了做到这一点,我们把这段基因插入到去除毒性的病毒体内.\N{\rasEng}In order to do that,we package the genes themselves into a harmless virus.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.12,0:47:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,但是要让病毒插入到正确的位置,\N{\rasEng}But to get the virus to the right place,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.36,0:47:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要把病毒注入到视网膜的下方.\N{\rasEng}we need to inject the virus underneath the retina.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.36,0:47:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然他的外科医生不能确定,这样一个前沿治疗的效果如何,\N{\rasEng}Though his surgeon isn't certain how effective this cutting-edge treatment will be,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.32,0:47:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,不进行干预,Abdullahi可能最终会完全失明.\N{\rasEng}without intervention,Abdullahi could eventually become totally blind.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.80,0:47:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这非凡的过程中希望实现的是\N{\rasEng}But what this remarkable procedure hopes to achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.96,0:47:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,没有什么比提供一个新的、未损坏部分的DNA来代替\N{\rasEng}is nothing less than delivering a new,undamaged section of DNA to do the work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.76,0:47:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Abdullahi有缺陷基因来做这工作.\N{\rasEng}of Abdullahi's faulty gene.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.24,0:48:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,好消息是,手术后,Abdullahi的视力开始提高.\N{\rasEng}The good news is that,since the operation,Abdullahi's vision has improved.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.36,0:48:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,这只是基因治疗进程中的一小步,但是我们有理由相信,\N{\rasEng}It's a small step on the gene therapy journey,but its champions believe
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.80,0:48:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,它最终可能会给我们带来巨大的好处.\N{\rasEng}it could eventually have benefits for a great number of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.60,0:48:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,成百上千个,不是吗？\N{\rasEng}It's got hundreds and thousands on it,hasn't it？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.84,0:48:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,就像Millie和Ruby这样患有哮喘的孩子,在英国占到了约百分之十.\N{\rasEng}Like about ten per cent of children in the UK,Millie and Ruby suffer from asthma.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.16,0:48:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,但是尽管这两个女孩的情况相似,\N{\rasEng}But while both girls have the condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.20,0:48:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Millie对药物的效果明显好于她的妹妹.\N{\rasEng}Millie responds a lot better to medication than her sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.24,0:48:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,（RUBY咳嗽）\N{\rasEng}RUBY COUGHS
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.08,0:48:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你有点咳嗽,是吗？你总是咳嗽吗？\N{\rasEng}You've got a bit of a cough,haven't you？ Do you always have a cough？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.00,0:48:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,对于Ruby,攻击导致无休止的进医院,并可能是致命的\N{\rasEng}'For Ruby,attacks result in endless dashes to hospital and could be fatal.'
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.00,0:48:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,（RUBY咳嗽）\N{\rasEng}RUBY COUGHS
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.72,0:48:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,面对你孩子的情况你无能为力.\N{\rasEng}There is nothing you can do to help your child.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.56,0:48:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,你想,"Ruby在某些时候,她会停止呼吸？"\N{\rasEng}You think,"At some point,is she going to stop breathing？"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.60,0:49:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,她们咳嗽这么多,她们正在生病,\N{\rasEng}They are coughing so much that they are being sick,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.12,0:49:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,她们的呼吸变得糟糕,你就得送她们去医院.\N{\rasEng}their breathing becomes worse and then you are going to hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.88,0:49:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这是你能想象到的最糟糕的感觉.\N{\rasEng}it is the worst feeling you can imagine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,但是Ruby是相当有活力性格,是不是？\N{\rasEng}But Ruby's quite a resilient character,isn't she？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.12,0:49:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,当然\N{\rasEng}Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.48,0:49:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,她很让人吃惊. 甚至当她最糟糕的时候,她也会给你一个微笑.\N{\rasEng}She's amazing. Even when she's at her worst,she'll give you a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.72,0:49:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Millie 和 Ruby 参与了一个研究项目\N{\rasEng}Millie and Ruby are taking part in a research project
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.44,0:49:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,该项目研究为什么某些病人比其他病人更容易痊愈.\N{\rasEng}which is trying to discover why some patients are easier to treat than others.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.40,0:49:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,在英国\N{\rasEng}Over 100,000 children
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.72,0:49:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,超过10万儿童哮喘患者\N{\rasEng}in the United Kingdom with asthma
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.08,0:49:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,携带者一个特定的变异基因\N{\rasEng}carry a particular gene change
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.16,0:49:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,让她们似乎更加敏感\N{\rasEng}which seems to make them much less responsive
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.04,0:49:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,对常见的哮喘药吸入器,我们使用的蓝色吸入器.\N{\rasEng}towards the commonest asthma-reliever inhaler,the blue inhaler that we use.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.72,0:49:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Swabs采样这对女孩的DNA,她们的基因,进行检测.\N{\rasEng}Swabs are taken so that the girls' DNA,their genes,can be examined.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.32,0:50:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,希望药物能和她们的基因相匹配,\N{\rasEng}The hope is that medicines can be matched to genes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.16,0:50:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,目前的试错方法来治疗\N{\rasEng}and that the current trial-and-error approach
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.92,0:50:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,像Ruby这样的人将成为历史.\N{\rasEng}to treating people like Ruby will be a thing of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.84,0:50:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,这个梦想是,最终,我们都会与药物治疗\N{\rasEng}The dream is that,eventually,we'll all be treated with medicines
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.40,0:50:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,与我们自己拥有的DNA完美的匹配.\N{\rasEng}that are a perfect match for our own unique DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.96,0:50:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,这项技术得以发展是受益于人类基因组项目\N{\rasEng}The technology that's developed since the human genome project means
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.44,0:50:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,排列个人基因图将变得越来越容易和经济.\N{\rasEng}that decoding an individual's genome is becoming easier and affordable.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.56,0:50:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,遗传学知识,是一个崭新的领域,理解我们的基因如何工作\N{\rasEng}Genetic knowledge is a new frontier and our understanding of how genes work
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.44,0:50:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,是自古代希腊时代最重要的医学进步之一.\N{\rasEng}is one of the most significant medical advances since the time of Ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.80,0:50:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这种方法的采用将彻底改变疾病治疗中的用药.\N{\rasEng}The methods it employs have applications that will revolutionise the treatment of disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.24,0:50:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Imperial学院的科学家在实验室里\N{\rasEng}Scientists working in this lab at Imperial College
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.24,0:50:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,正试图找到一个终结人类疾病的治疗.\N{\rasEng}are trying to find a cure for a devastating human disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.68,0:51:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,但是他们并不是开发新药,他们正试图了解如何长出新的组织.\N{\rasEng}But they're not developing medicines,they are trying to understand how to grow new tissues.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.76,0:51:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,我的同事 Michael Schneider是这一研究的国际领先者,\N{\rasEng}My colleague Michael Schneider is a world leader in this research,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.24,0:51:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他和他的团队已经取得了显著的进步.\N{\rasEng}and he and his team have made a remarkable advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.12,0:51:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他们从零开始培养出了跳动的心脏细胞.\N{\rasEng}They've created beating-heart cells from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.96,0:51:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,当你俯下身从显微镜中第一眼\N{\rasEng}When you first looked down the microscope
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.20,0:51:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,看到一个跳动的心脏细胞.\N{\rasEng}and saw a heart cell beating,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.88,0:51:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,你的反应是什么？\N{\rasEng}what was your reaction？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.48,0:51:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,当你看到这样的一群\N{\rasEng}When you see a cluster like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.16,0:51:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在培养皿中有力的跳动,\N{\rasEng}beating vigorously in the dish,it obviously stimulates your thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.64,0:51:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,这显然会刺激你去思考,如何应用这些信息,到复杂的心肌修复中的临床应用.\N{\rasEng}about how to apply that information to the complicated task of cardiac muscle repair in a clinical setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.92,0:51:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,十天前,这些\N{\rasEng}Ten days ago,those kinds of cells
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.52,0:51:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,未分化的胚胎干细胞\N{\rasEng}were undifferentiated embryonic stem cells
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.04,0:51:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,能不受限制的分化成身体的任何细胞.\N{\rasEng}that can become any cell in the body without restriction.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.76,0:52:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,当卵子受精时就产生了第一个干细胞.\N{\rasEng}Stem cells are among the first cells produced when an egg is fertilised.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.16,0:52:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,虽然开始时它们长的一模一样\N{\rasEng}Though they start off looking the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.40,0:52:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,很快它们就变成截然不同的东西 -\N{\rasEng}they soon turn into very different things -
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.64,0:52:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,骨骼、肌肉、头发、牙齿,神经,\N{\rasEng}bone,muscle,hair,teeth,nerves,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.40,0:52:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,所有不同类型的细胞构成了一个人.\N{\rasEng}all the different cell types that make up a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.60,0:52:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,通过了解这些转化如何运作的,\N{\rasEng}By understanding how these transformations work,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.92,0:52:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,像Michael这样的科学家,试图找到如何修补损伤或病变器官的方法.\N{\rasEng}scientists like Michael are trying to find out how to repair damaged or diseased organs.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.96,0:52:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,因此这项工作在干细胞领域中有多么重要？\N{\rasEng}So how important is this work in the field of stem cell biology？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.08,0:52:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,观看这个节目的人中40%将死于心血管疾病.\N{\rasEng}40% of the people watching this programme will die of cardiovascular disease.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.56,0:52:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,值得注意的是,心脏病实际上是细胞死亡,而没有新细胞来替换,\N{\rasEng}Taking that together with the fact that heart disease boils down to cell death without cell replacement,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.84,0:52:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,这就可以通过干细胞修复心脏\N{\rasEng}that makes cardiac repair by stem cells
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.28,0:52:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,这是干细胞研究领域中\N{\rasEng}one of the most important and promising areas
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.04,0:52:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,最重要最有前途的领域.\N{\rasEng}for stem cell research.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.52,0:52:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,到目前为止,已经因为对干细胞研究\N{\rasEng}So far,there have been few treatments developed
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.80,0:52:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,而发展出一些治疗方法,但一些研究人员甚至希望他们最终将能够\N{\rasEng}because of work on stem cells,but some researchers even hope that eventually they'll be able
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.20,0:53:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,用培植器官来替换,或至少帮助身体自我修复.\N{\rasEng}to grow replacement organs,or at least help the body repair itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.04,0:53:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,极少数人反对人类胚胎研究,因为它破坏人类胚胎.\N{\rasEng}A tiny minority are opposed to human embryo research because it damages human embryos.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.56,0:53:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,他们有道理,但实际上我认为这是道义,\N{\rasEng}They have a point,but to my mind it's actually an ethical imperative
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.48,0:53:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,试图拯救生命,这是一个方法.\N{\rasEng}to try to save lives and this is one way of doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.52,0:53:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,'我最后的科学进步是非常接近我的心.\N{\rasEng}'My final scientific advance is very close to my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.56,0:53:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,'这是一些我职业生涯中最投入的\N{\rasEng}'It's something to which I've devoted most of my career.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.40,0:53:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,'每一个这些儿童的生命开始于一个试管\N{\rasEng}'Every single one of these children's lives began in a test tube
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.32,0:53:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,'或培养皿. 他们是试管婴儿.他们不是在子宫里,而是在实验室里成为受精卵'\N{\rasEng}'or a dish. They are IVF children. They come from eggs fertilised not in the womb but in the laboratory.'
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.92,0:53:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这真可怕！\N{\rasEng}That was really frightening!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.24,0:53:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,'如果不是因为生命科学研究的最早阶段,他们不会在这里.'\N{\rasEng}'None of them would be here if it wasn't for scientific research into the earliest stages of life.'
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.96,0:53:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯,这是粉红色的.这不是真正的红色.\N{\rasEng}Well,it is sort of pink. It's not really red.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.44,0:53:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,你想要粉色,现在？ 不？ 你很特别！\N{\rasEng}Would you allow pink,then？ No？ You're very particular!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.40,0:54:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,'虽然我曾参与了这项研究,\N{\rasEng}'And although I was involved in that research,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.32,0:54:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,'我必须承认,在当时,我没有意识到它的重要性.'\N{\rasEng}'I have to confess that,at the time,I didn't appreciate its significance.'
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.60,0:54:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,我并没有想到它会真的变得如此重要.\N{\rasEng}I didn't think it was really going to be very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.08,0:54:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我没有想到试管婴儿是一项科技\N{\rasEng}I didn't think that IVF was a technology
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.56,0:54:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这真的可以用来治疗不育症.\N{\rasEng}that would really make any difference to infertility treatment.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.48,0:54:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,看看我曾犯了多大的错误……\N{\rasEng}Look how wrong I was...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.48,0:54:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,这些孩子.他们是世界上上百万个试管婴儿中的一些.\N{\rasEng}all these babies. There are about a million IVF babies around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.64,0:54:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,在二十世纪八十年代,我和我的同事开发了一个实验\N{\rasEng}In the 1980s,my colleagues and I developed an experimental IVF technique
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.32,0:54:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,来筛选试管婴儿技术在胚胎发育的遗传疾病.\N{\rasEng}to screen for genetic diseases in the developing embryo.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.84,0:54:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Christine Munday的第一个孩子Justin,是一个重度残疾人,\N{\rasEng}Christine Munday's first son Justin was severely handicapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.16,0:54:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,发现她携带有遗传病\N{\rasEng}and it was discovered that she carries a genetic condition
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.16,0:54:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,这意味着她的任何一个儿子非常有可能\N{\rasEng}which means it is very likely that any of her male children
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.24,0:54:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,继承同样的问题.\N{\rasEng}would inherit the same problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.04,0:54:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,为取得这一突破,我们已经努力了9年\N{\rasEng}We've been trying for nine years
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.60,0:55:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们今后可以有机会.\N{\rasEng}for this breakthrough to come so that we could have another chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.20,0:55:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,1990年,我们筛选了她受精胚胎,以确保她有一个女孩.\N{\rasEng}In 1990,we screened her fertilised embryos to ensure that she had a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.60,0:55:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Rebecca现在19岁了.\N{\rasEng}Rebecca is now 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.32,0:55:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,你妈妈是非常勇敢.我不知道你能否意识到这一点,\N{\rasEng}Your mum was wonderfully brave. I don't know if you realise that,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.56,0:55:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们当时所作的是\N{\rasEng}because what we were doing was
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.92,0:55:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,纯粹的实验,我们不知道这样做是否有用\N{\rasEng}a very,very experimental procedure and we had no idea if it was going to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.12,0:55:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,你还记得,我们不能保证你会有一个不受影响的孩子.\N{\rasEng}work or not. As you remember,we couldn't guarantee that you wouldn't have a child who wasn't affected.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.52,0:55:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,不.对于我,那不是勇敢,你知道,孩子可能会以某种方式出现缺陷,\N{\rasEng}No. To us,it wasn't brave,you know,the baby could have been damaged
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.84,0:55:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但我从来没有担心过那边一点.\N{\rasEng}in some way but I never,ever worried about that side of it at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.04,0:55:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,我有充分的信心,相信你会成功的.\N{\rasEng}I had my whole confidence that you would actually get it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.20,0:55:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,是啊,有趣,不是吗？我当时可没什么信心.\N{\rasEng}Yeah,funny,isn't it？ I don't think that I had that confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.64,0:55:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,作为一个体外受精的孩子是否让你感觉有什么不同？\N{\rasEng}Does having been born as a result of in vitro fertilisation make you feel any different？
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.56,0:55:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我很感动.\N{\rasEng}I'm quite humbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.96,0:56:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的家庭,这是很重要的突破.\N{\rasEng}For our family,it's been quite crucial for this breakthrough.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.48,0:56:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道？当然,当然.\N{\rasEng}You know？ Of course,of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.36,0:56:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不那样做,今天我就不会有Rebecca.她不总是这么说.\N{\rasEng}I wouldn't have Rebecca today if it wasn't for that. She doesn't always say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.56,0:56:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,对于我,见到你的时候,真的很感人.\N{\rasEng}For me,it's genuinely a very moving occasion actually to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.12,0:56:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,对我来说非常特别.\N{\rasEng}Very special for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.16,0:56:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,'20年前,有相当多的人反对这项工作'\N{\rasEng}'20 years ago,there was considerable opposition from people hoping to stop such work.'
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.44,0:56:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,那是什么？\N{\rasEng}What's that？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.08,0:56:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那是你吗？\N{\rasEng}Was that you？
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.96,0:56:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,'但是在英国,立法非常迅速.\N{\rasEng}'But in the UK,legislation was hugely positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.28,0:56:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,'它使我们带来希望,不仅仅是像Christine,而是成千上万\N{\rasEng}'And it has enabled us give hope,not just to people like Christine,but also to hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.88,0:56:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,'由于某种原因没有孩子的家庭.'\N{\rasEng}'of families who otherwise couldn't have had children.'
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.96,0:56:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,ALL: Cheese!\N{\rasEng}ALL: Cheese!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.00,0:57:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,好了,这就是我的科学进步名单.现在该你说了.\N{\rasEng}Well,that concludes my list. Now it's time for you to have your say.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.20,0:57:06.28,Default,,0,0,0,,刚才观看过的十大科学进步中你认为那一项是最重要的？\N{\rasEng}Which of the ten scientific advances we've looked at do you think is the most important？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.76,0:57:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,是创造了上百万生命的试管婴儿,或是给予厚望的干细胞研究？\N{\rasEng}Is it the millions of lives created by IVF,or the huge promise of stem cell research？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.24,0:57:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,拯救生命的MRI是你的最爱？\N{\rasEng}Is your favourite the life-saving MRI machine？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.64,0:57:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,或是强大的微芯片？\N{\rasEng}Or the mighty microchip？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.16,0:57:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,你认为避孕药为我们做的,比高能激光多得多？\N{\rasEng}Do you think the contraceptive pill has done more for us than the giant laser ever will？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.24,0:57:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,或者更能鼓舞你的是能够重建我们自己的仿生学？\N{\rasEng}Or is it our ability to rebuild ourselves with bionics that inspires you the most？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.72,0:57:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你能说全球互联网的力量,能击败读懂拥有巨大潜力的我们的基因图？\N{\rasEng}Can you say the global power of the Internet beats the huge potential of understanding more about our genes？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.44,0:57:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,抑或是令人难以置信的大爆炸理论胜过它们？\N{\rasEng}Or does the mind-boggling big-bang theory trump them all？
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.92,0:57:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,到我们的网站上\N{\rasEng}Go to our website to vote for the scientific advance
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.60,0:57:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,投出你心目中的最重大科学进步. 访问...\N{\rasEng}you think has been the most significant. Visit...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.08,0:58:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在网站上有十大科学进步的提示.\N{\rasEng}There's a reminder of the top ten advancements on the website.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.64,0:58:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,在你上网投票前.我觉得我得先把我的卡放在桌子上.\N{\rasEng}Before you vote on-line,I feel I should put my cards on the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.64,0:58:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,我不愿说这十大科学进步哪一个是我的最佳\N{\rasEng}I'm reluctant to say which of these ten advances is my greatest,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.28,0:58:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,只是可能,我可能会选择大爆炸的研究.\N{\rasEng}but just possibly,I might plump for the research on big bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.16,0:58:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,似乎没用,但它带来的知识\N{\rasEng}It might seem useless,yet the knowledge it brings
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.64,0:58:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎、肯定会对人类产生无法预料的影响.\N{\rasEng}will almost certainly have unforeseen consequences for humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.68,0:58:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,也许,了解宇宙要好一点\N{\rasEng}Just possibly,understanding the universe a little better
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.84,0:58:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,会帮助我们这个物种继续蓬勃发展.\N{\rasEng}will help our species to continue to flourish.
